 :tx/rationale "Create task: TSV-TEST (REVISED): Comprehensive TSV verification — json_to_tsv proptest + ACP rendering test + E2E script (INV-INTERFACE-001, INV-BUDGET-006). BACKGROUND: TSV correctness requires verifying the json_to_tsv pure function AND the ACP-aware rendering path. APPROACH: (1) Proptest for json_to_tsv: arbitrary JSON Value → tsv render → every line has same tab count as header (field count invariant). (2) Proptest: json_to_tsv round-trip — parse TSV back, field values match JSON source. (3) Unit test: ACP JSON with _acp field → TSV renders action + context blocks. (4) Unit test: non-ACP JSON with 'tasks' array → TSV renders header + rows. (5) Unit test: tab characters in values → escaped to spaces (no field corruption). (6) Unit test: empty JSON → empty TSV (graceful degradation). (7) E2E script scripts/e2e_tsv_output.sh with 15+ checks: (a) braid task list --format tsv | wc -l == task_count+1. (b) cut -f1 extracts valid t-* IDs. (c) sort -t TAB -k2 -n sorts by priority. (d) braid status --format tsv | grep fitness extracts F(S). (e) braid task ready --format tsv | head -2 shows highest-impact task. (f) braid query --attribute :task/status --format tsv | wc -l counts datoms. (g) braid witness status --format tsv has correct column count. (h) braid topology plan --agents 2 --format tsv shows agent assignments. (i) --format tsv --budget 10 produces same output as --budget 10000 (budget bypass). (j) braid task list --format tsv | awk -F'\\t' '{print NF}' | sort -u outputs single number (field count consistency). (k) Empty store: braid task list --format tsv produces header only. ACCEPTANCE: (A) All proptests pass (100 iterations). (B) E2E: 15+ checks all pass. (C) No existing tests regress. DEPENDS-ON: TSV-3-REVISED. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/budget.rs (tests) + scripts/e2e_tsv_output.sh"
